        <div class="refund-box">
            <h3>üìã Refund Guidelines</h3>
           <h3>üìã Refund Policy Overview</h3>

<p>
    <strong>Refunds from Tutors Link are only available within the first month of service.</strong>
</p>

<h3>Demo Class Refund</h3>
<p>
    If a student and tutor attend a demo class and either party decides not to continue for any reason,
    the student is eligible for a <strong>100% refund</strong>, provided no Tutors Link policies were violated
    (for example, sharing contact information during the demo class).
</p>

<h3>First Week Refund</h3>
<p>
    If the student and tutor decide to continue after the demo class but later stop within the first week
    due to a valid issue (such as the tutor not attending sessions or the student behaving inappropriately),
    the student will receive:
</p>

<ul style="text-align: left; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <li>A refund for all unattended classes</li>
    <li>A refund for classes that had confirmed issues</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    Proof may be required. Tutors will still be paid for classes that were completed properly.
</p>

